                    Existing court fines
                </h1>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Criminalization
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>If your patient has outstanding court fines that, in your assessment, impact their medical or mental health, this form generator will help you to write a letter advocating for your patient’s court fines to be eliminated or reduced.</p>
                <p>For fines that have already been imposed, patients are typically ordered to make monthly payments according to a pre-specified payment plan. When patients attend court to develop this payment plan, they often do not have an attorney with them, nor is a public defender assigned to the case. This is why the letter must be submitted by the patient directly to the judge.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Documents</h2>
                <ol>
